<p class="P1"><span class="T3">1.</span><span class="T1"> </span><span class="T3">INTRODUCTION AND INTERPRETATION</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">1.1 The party listed as applicant ("Applicant") in the application form (“Application”) to which these Terms and Conditions ("Terms and Conditions") are attached wishes to borrow funds on a short-term basis and has duly completed the Application to apply for a loan ("Loan").</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">1.2 For purposes of this document, the Borrower will be referred to herein as “You, Your or Yourself”. “Law” means common law, statutes, and regulations and any subsidiary legislation prevailing from time to time in the Republic of South Africa; “Working Day” means any day other than Saturday, Sunday or official public holiday in the Republic of South Africa.</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T3">2.</span><span class="T1"> </span><span class="T3">APPLICATION AND APPROVAL</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">2.1 After assessing the Application duly completed by You and being satisfied that You are not over-indebted Atlas Finance may approve your Application and agree to lend You the amount set out in the Pre-Agreement Statement and Quotation (“the Quotation”) to which these terms and conditions (“Terms and Conditions”) are attached and form part, Atlas Finance will send you an SMS or email to advise You if Your application was successful or not.</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T4">2.2 If and when </span><span class="T1">Atlas Finance </span><span class="T4">approve</span><span class="T1">s Y</span><span class="T4">our </span><span class="T1">A</span><span class="T4">pplication, actual </span><span class="T1">transfer </span><span class="T4">of the </span><span class="T1">L</span><span class="T4">oan </span><span class="T1">A</span><span class="T4">mount </span><span class="T1">to You </span><span class="T4">is subject to:</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T4">2.2.1 </span><span class="T1">Atlas Finance </span><span class="T4">ensuring that the information </span><span class="T1">Y</span><span class="T4">ou gave </span><span class="T1">it </span><span class="T4">was not inaccurate or deficient in any respect (if </span><span class="T1">Atlas Finance </span><span class="T4">discover</span><span class="T1">s</span><span class="T4"> that it was, then the Agreement will be void and </span><span class="T1">where appropriate may </span><span class="T4">be reported to credit reference and fraud agencies);</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T4">2.2.2 </span><span class="T1">Atlas Finance </span><span class="T4">checking </span><span class="T1">and assessing </span><span class="T4">the affordability of the </span><span class="T1">L</span><span class="T4">oan</span><span class="T1">; and</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T4">2.2.3 </span><span class="T1">completion of the payment instruction ("Payment Instruction") in favour of Atlas Finance.</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T3">3.</span><span class="T1"> </span><span class="T3">ACCEPTANCE OF QUOTATION</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">3.1 You have 5 (five) working days to accept the Quotation. Should your financial/personal circumstances or information provided by You change from the day the Quotation was given but before the Loan is paid to You, Atlas Finance may in its sole and absolute discretion either refuse to give You the Loan or provide You with a revised Quotation.</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">3.2 You are the only person who has the right to accept the Loan Agreement. If You accept the Loan Agreement, You must click the Quotation by clicking on the "</span><span class="T6">I Accept</span><span class="T1">" box on Your screen. By typing your name in the relevant box and clicking "</span><span class="T6">I Accept</span><span class="T1">" You will be deemed to have signed and accepted the Quotation and be legally bound by the Quotation, Terms and Conditions and the Application