 as set out in the Quotation.</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">6.2 You agree to repay Atlas Finance the Total Amount Repayable on the date on which You have chosen in the Application to repay same (“Repayment Date”).</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">6.3 Atlas Finance will collect this payment on the Repayment Date by way of direct debit from Your bank account in terms of the Payment Instruction. You must ensure that there are sufficient funds in the bank account to recover payment on the Repayment Date.</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">6.4 If Atlas Finance is unsuccessful in collecting the Total Amount Repayable on the Repayment Date, it may try to debit Your bank account at a later stage and on more than one occasion on the Repayment Date for all or any part of the Total Amount Repayable as it determines necessary until the Total Amount Repayable has been paid.</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">6</span><span class="T4">.5 Your </span><span class="T1">payment to Atlas Finance will be allocated on the day it is received and applied in the following order: fees, then charges, then interest and finally to the capital (being the Loan Amount).</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">6.6 You may not withhold or deduct any payment owing to Atlas Finance for any reason whatsoever.</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">6.7 You will not be entitled to set-off any counterclaim that You may have against Atlas Finance or any other person as a reason for non-payment of the Total Amount Repayable or any part thereof.</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">6.8 Should You default, the period of the Loan may further be extended to allow You to settle your indebtedness over the additional period at Atlas Finance’s sole and absolute discretion and this indulgence will not be construed as a waiver of any of Atlas Finance’s rights to enforce the Loan Agreement.</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T3">7.</span><span class="T1"> </span><span class="T3">FEES AND CHARGES</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">7.1 In addition to the Loan Amount You will be responsible to pay to Atlas Finance the fees, charges and interest referred to in the Quotation. We will notify You of any changes to the fees or charges in writing within 5 working days of when such changes will apply.</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T3">8.</span><span class="T1"> </span><span class="T3">INTEREST</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">8.1 You will pay interest on any amount still due to Atlas Finance from when it is due until it is actually paid at the interest rate shown in the Quotation ("Interest Rate").</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">8.2 Interest at the Interest Rate will be calculated from the date of payment of the Loan Amount, capitalised monthly over the repayment period and debited on the last day of each month, (thus being calculated in arrears). Should the Borrower fail to pay any amount which is due under the Loan Agreement by the due date and/or should Atlas Finance grant the Borrower an extension for repayment, interest calculated at the Interest Rate aforesaid will be charged on such unpaid amount/s in arrears or default interest until such time as all amounts owing by You to Atlas Finance are repaid in full.</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">8</span><span class="T4">.3 </span><span class="T1">In addition, Atlas Finance will claim interest at the Interest Rate, or as prescribed by a Court, in respect of all collection costs, enforcement expenses, due and payable by You to it if it proceeds with a legal action.</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T3">9.</span><span class="T1"> </span><span class="T3">DEFAULT ADMINISTRATION, COLLECTION COSTS AND ENFORCEMENT EXPENSES</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">9.1 If You default in any of Your obligations under the Loan Agreement You will be responsible for Enforcement Expenses and Collection Costs allowed in terms of applicable Law that are incurred by Atlas Finance in the enforcement of this Loan Agreement, and specifically for all legal costs on the attorney and client scale. Such Expenses and Costs will form part of the Settlement Value.</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">9.2 Subject to any Law to the contrary, all expenses and charges referred to in this clause 8 will bear interest at the Interest Rate from the date on which they are due until the date of actual payment thereof.</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T3">10.</span><span class="T1"> </span><span class="T3">EARLY SETTLEMENT</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">You may settle the loan in full at any time before the Repayment Date, with or without notice, by paying the Settlement Value to Atlas Finance. No penalty will be charged for early settlement of the Loan.</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T3">11.</span><span class="T1"> </span><span class="T3">STATEMENTS OF ACCOUNT</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">Statements of Account will be sent via email and can be found on the “</span><span class="T6">My Account</span><span class="T1">” section of the Website. Non receipt of a statement by You will not be a cause to withhold any payment due.</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T3">12.</span><span class="T1"> </span><span class="T3">REPAYMENT EVENT</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">12.1 Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained herein, Atlas Finance may at any time terminate this Loan Agreement and claim payment of the Settlement Value from You if:</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">12.1.1 You commit any act of insolvency contemplated in the Insolvency Act, 1936 or are sequestrated [whether provisionally or finally] or are placed under administration in </span><span class="T1">terms of section 74 of the Magistrates’ Courts Act, 1944 or become subject to debt review in terms of the National Credit Act (“the Act”); or</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">12.1.2 You are in default of this Loan Agreement and have failed to rectify the default as required in clause 12; or</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">12.1.3 Your employment by the employer is terminated for any reason; or</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">12.1.4 You retire prior to payment of the Settlement Value to Atlas Finance</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">(each of the aforementioned events will constitute a “Repayment Event”).</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">12.2 Upon the occurrence of a Repayment Event the full Settlement Value under the Loan Agreement, whether or not such amount is then due and payable shall immediately become payable to Atlas Finance.</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T5">1</span><span class="T3">3</span><span class="T5">.</span><span class="T4"> </span><span class="T3">DEFAULT</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T4">1</span><span class="T1">3</span><span class="T4">.1 </span><span class="T1">You are in default of the Loan Agreement if You:</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">13.1.1 do something You have agreed not to do or do not do something You have agreed to do, under the Loan Agreement;</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">13.1.2 give Atlas Finance incorrect, misleading or deceptive information in connection with this Loan Agreement in a way which would have affected Atlas Finance’s decision to lend You money;</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">13.1.3 have acted fraudulently or dishonestly in connection with this Loan Agreement; or</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">13.1.4 commit a breach of any of the declarations provided by You to Atlas Finance;</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">13.1.5 die; or</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">13.1.6 fail to make payment of any amount due in terms of this Loan Agreement.</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">13.2 If You are in default, Atlas Finance will give You a written notice (“Default Notice”) as required by Section 129 of the Act electronically advising You of the default and advising You that You may refer the matter to an alternative dispute resolution mechanism, ombud or consumer court, or resolve it with Atlas Finance.</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">13.3 If You have been in default for 20 (twenty) Working Days and at least 10 (ten) Working Days have expired since Atlas Finance gave You Default Notice and You have not responded to the Default Notice, or rejected Atlas Finance’s proposals, Atlas Finance will be able to take action for payment of the Settlement Value and You will be liable to pay us Enforcement Expenses and Collection Costs as allowed in Law and referred to in the Quotation.</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">13.4 Where You cannot pay Your debts and if You do not consult, or refuse to consult with a debt counsellor, then Atlas Finance will be entitled but not obliged to hand the Loan Agreement over to its attorneys or a debt collector registered in terms of the Debt Collectors Act of 1998 for the collection of the Settlement Value.</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">13.5 In addition, upon the occurrence of a default Atlas Finance will charge interest at the Interest Rate set out in the Quotation on any amounts due, owing and payable to Atlas Finance from the date that it became due for payment, to the date of actual payment thereof.</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">13.6 You have also agreed that Atlas Finance may submit an adverse report of Your default to a credit bureau, setting out particulars thereof. If this is the case at least 20 (twenty) Working Days’ notice will be given to You prior to reporting any adverse information to a credit bureau and You will be entitled to a copy of the adverse report upon request.</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">13.7 If You experience difficulty in meeting Your repayments, You are invited to contact Atlas Finance without delay. You also have a right to apply to a debt counsellor to be considered for in terms of Section 86 of the Act to be declared over-indebted. A fee might be payable to such debt counsellor who will then evaluate the extent of Your indebtedness and may attempt to assist in the re-arrangement of Your debt if You are in fact over indebted.</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T3">14. TEMPORARY DISABILITY</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">14.1 If, as a result of Your temporary disablement, or for any other reason, payment of Your salary by your employer is temporarily suspended, then, if applicable, You shall ensure that any insurer or third party which is paying a benefit in lieu of the suspended salary to You or on Your behalf, deducts from such benefit and pays to Atlas Finance any amount due in terms of the Loan Agreement during the period concerned.</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">14.2 Should such insurer or third party fail to make payment to Atlas Finance, then Atlas Finance will be entitled to act pursuant to clause 12 above.</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T3">15.</span><span class="T1"> </span><span class="T3">APPOINTMENT OF SYNDICATED DEBT COLLECTORS</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">15.1 The Borrower hereby authorises Atlas Finance to appoint Syndicated Debt Collectors (Pty) Ltd (“SDC”) (Reg no: 2008/023231/07) (VAT No: 435025 5990) [or its successors-in-title] to administer any Loan under this Loan Agreement and to collect and pay over any initiation and service fees, insurance premiums and/or default administration and other charges in respect of this Loan to Atlas Finance or any party Atlas Finance may in its sole discretion elect.</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T1">15.2 In order to fulfil its functions as administrator of the Loan, the Borrower understands and agrees that SDC shall be empowered by Atlas Finance to do all such things and take all such action as may be legally allowed in order to comply with its obligations as administrator of the Loan.</span></p><p class="P1"><span class="T5">1</span><span class="T3">6</span><span class="T5">.</sp